{"word":"τηρέω","slug":"τηρέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τηρέω</b></el> <el>(τηρέω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ήσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>τῆρος</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to watch over, protect, guard</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be constantly guarded</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>; <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>τηρήσομαι</el> in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to take care that . .</i> , <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to give heed to, watch narrowly, observe</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>τὰς ἁμαρτίας</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to watch for</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>; <el>παραστείχοντα τηρήσας</el> <i>having watched for</i> him as he was passing by, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to watch, keep watch</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to watch</i> or <i>look out</i>, so as to . . , <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><i>to observe</i> or <i>keep</i> an engagement, <b><a href='S:Isocrates'>Isocr.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>τ. εἰρήνην</el> <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}